<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-515-009  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 515 009.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Oct 8 1990 n290 p42(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technology for tots.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Caldwell, Bruce.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Education Technology Trust (NETT), formed in 1988, ishelping to promote the use of technology in the classroomthroughout the US.andP;  On Oct 20, 1990, the group will broadcasttheir goals in a teleconference underwritten by IBM in New York onWNYE.andP;  Other teleconferences have been aired in Philadelphia andDallas.andP;  The group has applied for a federal grant.andP;  The grouppromotes the idea that the application of technology in earlychildhood helps children keep their natural curiosity.andP;  NETT willundertake larger projects, national in scope, that will attractfederal and corporate funds for school technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Elementary SchoolsTechnologyMicrocomputersEducationComputer-Assisted InstructionGovernment FundingNational Education Technology Trust.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>